        "text": "Clean Electricity for 700 Households and Clinics in Rural Communities of Lesotho\n\nThe construction of the mini-grids has been generously supported with the funds from the Global Environment Facility (GEF). Additional funding was sourced by OnePower Lesotho. This is implemented by the Department of Energy under the Sustainable Energy for All project with support from UNDP Lesotho.\n\nExploring Innovation Diffusion Platforms for Experiments’ Scaling within the UN and Government’s Development Work\n\nThe AccLab is looking at ways to expand innovations in Lesotho to scale and advance development. The Lab took partners to various sites to explore ways in which they can partner with UNDP Lesotho to up-scale experiments.\n\nI am an Elegant Grasshopper: I am a farmer’s friend!\n\nThe Lesotho Accelerator Lab discovered that grasshoppers can be used as safe and effective pesticides and/or insecticides for certain crops. They partnered with the National University of Lesotho to conduct scientific research on this indigenous farming practice to advance sustainable farming."
